AuthorizationAlreadyExistsFault.documentation: The specified CIDRIP or EC2 security group is already authorized for the specified DB security group.

AuthorizationNotFoundFault.documentation:
Specified CIDRIP or EC2 security group is not authorized for the specified DB security group.

RDS may not also be authorized via IAM to perform necessary actions on your behalf.

AuthorizationQuotaExceededFault.documentation: DB security group authorization quota has been reached.

DBInstanceAlreadyExistsFault.documentation: User already has a DB instance with the given identifier.

DBInstanceNotFoundFault.documentation: DBInstanceIdentifier does not refer to an existing DB instance.

DBLogFileNotFoundFault.documentation: LogFileName does not refer to an existing DB log file.

DBParameterGroupAlreadyExistsFault.documentation: A DB parameter group with the same name exists.

DBParameterGroupNotFoundFault.documentation: DBParameterGroupName does not refer to an existing DB parameter group.

DBParameterGroupQuotaExceededFault.documentation: Request would result in user exceeding the allowed number of DB parameter groups.

DBSecurityGroupAlreadyExistsFault.documentation: A DB security group with the name specified in DBSecurityGroupName already exists.

DBSecurityGroupNotFoundFault.documentation: DBSecurityGroupName does not refer to an existing DB security group.

DBSecurityGroupNotSupportedFault.documentation: A DB security group is not allowed for this action.

DBSecurityGroupQuotaExceededFault.documentation: Request would result in user exceeding the allowed number of DB security groups.

DBSnapshotAlreadyExistsFault.documentation: DBSnapshotIdentifier is already used by an existing snapshot.

DBSnapshotNotFoundFault.documentation: DBSnapshotIdentifier does not refer to an existing DB snapshot.

DBSubnetGroupAlreadyExistsFault.documentation: DBSubnetGroupName is already used by an existing DB subnet group.

DBSubnetGroupDoesNotCoverEnoughAZs.documentation: Subnets in the DB subnet group should cover at least two Availability Zones unless there is only one Availability Zone.

DBSubnetGroupNotAllowedFault.documentation: Indicates that the DBSubnetGroup should not be specified while creating read replicas that lie in the same region as the source instance.

DBSubnetGroupNotFoundFault.documentation: DBSubnetGroupName does not refer to an existing DB subnet group.

DBSubnetGroupQuotaExceededFault.documentation: Request would result in user exceeding the allowed number of DB subnet groups.

DBSubnetQuotaExceededFault.documentation: Request would result in user exceeding the allowed number of subnets in a DB subnet groups.

DBUpgradeDependencyFailureFault.documentation: The DB upgrade failed because a resource the DB depends on could not be modified.

EventSubscriptionQuotaExceededFault.documentation: You have reached the maximum number of event subscriptions.

InstanceQuotaExceededFault.documentation: Request would result in user exceeding the allowed number of DB instances.

InsufficientDBInstanceCapacityFault.documentation: Specified DB instance class is not available in the specified Availability Zone.

InvalidDBInstanceStateFault.documentation: The specified DB instance is not in the available state.

InvalidDBParameterGroupStateFault.documentation: The DB parameter group is in use or is in an invalid state. If you are attempting to delete the parameter group, you cannot delete it when the parameter group is in this state.

InvalidDBSecurityGroupStateFault.documentation: The state of the DB security group does not allow deletion.

InvalidDBSnapshotStateFault.documentation: The state of the DB snapshot does not allow deletion.

InvalidDBSubnetGroupFault.documentation: Indicates the DBSubnetGroup does not belong to the same VPC as that of an existing cross region read replica of the same source instance.

InvalidDBSubnetGroupStateFault.documentation: The DB subnet group cannot be deleted because it is in use.

InvalidDBSubnetStateFault.documentation: The DB subnet is not in the available state.

InvalidEventSubscriptionStateFault.documentation: This error can occur if someone else is modifying a subscription. You should retry the action.

InvalidOptionGroupStateFault.documentation: The option group is not in the available state.

InvalidRestoreFault.documentation: Cannot restore from vpc backup to non-vpc DB instance.

InvalidSubnet.documentation: The requested subnet is invalid, or multiple subnets were requested that are not all in a common VPC.

InvalidVPCNetworkStateFault.documentation: DB subnet group does not cover all Availability Zones after it is created because users' change.

OptionGroupAlreadyExistsFault.documentation: The option group you are trying to create already exists.

OptionGroupNotFoundFault.documentation: The specified option group could not be found.

OptionGroupQuotaExceededFault.documentation: The quota of 20 option groups was exceeded for this AWS account.

PointInTimeRestoreNotEnabledFault.documentation: SourceDBInstanceIdentifier refers to a DB instance with BackupRetentionPeriod equal to 0.

ProvisionedIopsNotAvailableInAZFault.documentation: Provisioned IOPS not available in the specified Availability Zone.

ReservedDBInstanceAlreadyExistsFault.documentation: User already has a reservation with the given identifier.

ReservedDBInstanceNotFoundFault.documentation: The specified reserved DB Instance not found.

ReservedDBInstanceQuotaExceededFault.documentation: Request would exceed the user's DB Instance quota.

SNSInvalidTopicFault.documentation: SNS has responded that there is a problem with the SND topic specified.

SNSNoAuthorizationFault.documentation: You do not have permission to publish to the SNS topic ARN.

SNSTopicArnNotFoundFault.documentation: The SNS topic ARN does not exist.

SnapshotQuotaExceededFault.documentation: Request would result in user exceeding the allowed number of DB snapshots.

SourceNotFoundFault.documentation: The requested source could not be found.

StorageQuotaExceededFault.documentation: Request would result in user exceeding the allowed amount of storage available across all DB instances.

SubnetAlreadyInUse.documentation: The DB subnet is already in use in the Availability Zone.
